kubernetes is a cloud based autoscaling solution
that allows multiple microservices to connect and 
scale easily with minimal downtime. Kubernetes also
allows self-healing services and in a way automates
some form of disaster recovery by ensuring the right
amount of resources are allocated for each microservice


kubernetes is also known as k8s, we will practice deploying
a simple project on k8s at the end of this tutorial but
firstly let us configure 
